  "caption": "Figure 3. Fimoviridae. Phylogenetic tree constructed with amino acid sequences encoded by RNA1 (RdRP) of members of the family Fimoviridae , using MUSCLE alignment and Maximum Likelihood method implemented in MEGA11 ( Tamura et al., 2013 ). The GenBank accession numbers of the sequences used are reported next to the virus names. Bootstrap values above 50% are shown at branch points, with 1000 replicates. Viruses with white circles are putative fimoviruses of the family Fimoviridae that still need to be officially recognized. Tomato spotted wilt virus was used as an outgroup species.",
